args: Warm sunlight and a gentle breeze...\nPerfect conditions for a day of fishing!
It's been so long since we were all able\nto fish together. We gotta milk this day\nfor everything it's worth!
Former Sealer Who Loves to Fish
Indeed. I was delighted to discover that\nothers in this castle shared my passion.
Former Sailor Who Loves to Fish
So long as we've three skilled fishers\namong us, why not make this interesting\nand see who can land the most?
Hee hee ha ha hee! A contest, is it?\nNow THAT sounds like fun.
That suits me fine. I am always eager for a\nchance to show off the fishing skills my\nfather taught me.
Ah, a mighty pull! I expect I've snared a\nbig one here! Haaaaaah!

'Twas a great fish indeed! Ah, but there is
no greater feeling than seizing victory
at the end of a hard-fought duel.
Still, I wonder how my rivals fare...?
Yesss! Just look how these finny critters\nflock to my special homemade bait!

So you rely not on talent, but tools, eh?
I should have expected as much from one
who trusts in relics as much as you.
But as for Thaniel...
Hmm? Ah, behold that faint ripple on the\nwater's surface. That shows me just where\nto cast my line. Hah!
I knew it! That WAS a school of fish!
Truly, Thaniel, you are a man of the sea.\nYou perceive much beneath the surface.

Between these two potent warriors of
rod and reel, it is clear I have a great
battle on my hands. And yet, I would
not think to have it any other way.
It wouldn't do to make it easy for you.\nAnd when it comes to fishing, I have no\ngreat shortage of skill.
Even my stern father couldn't help\nbut praise my angling talents!
You might have talent coming out the...\nEr, you might have a lot of talent,\nbut I've got WAY more experience!
I've been fishing for...what? 300 years?\n400? Gosh, it's been so dang long,\nI can barely remember.
Regardless, I definitely know my way\naround a lure, and victory will be mine!
Ah, now things are getting interesting!\nMethinks it is time to remove the kid\ngloves and strike for true.
Fishing is but a duel between man and\nbeast—and as a samurai who lives for\nthe thrill of battle, I'll not be defeated!
I must allow myself access to the\nmost forbidden art in my arsenal...\nDual-wielding fishing poles!
Wait, time out! You're planning to catch\ntwice as many fish by using twice as many\nrods? Is that even a thing?!
Ah ha ha! The ability to wield two blades\nas if they were part of my body is at the\nvery heart of my swordcraft.
By tapping into that selfsame talent,\nI can wield two poles with equal ease!
Okay, I guess that IS a thing.\nBut how am I supposed to—BWAAAH!
Thaniel? Did you just fall in the water?\nEr, you need some help there, buddy?
Thaniel? Why do you not pull yourself\nup onto that nearby ledge?
Now he's diving UNDER the water!
He does not appear to be drowning,\nexactly. But what IS he doing...?
Ha! Yes, well. My apologies for that.\nWhat a fluky accident. ...Huh?
Well, I'll be. My pockets are full of fish.
You caught fish with your bare hands?!
Bzzzt! No way, mister! That is SO not fair!
Y-you misunderstand the circumstances!\nIt was coincidence! Mere coincidence!\nSuch things happen to everyone, yes?
Okay, that's it. If we're turning this\nhonorable competition into a total\ncheat-fest, then I'm going all the way!
O power universal, heed my solemn\ndecree! Convert my words of speech!
Fiiishies! I've got yummy baaait for you!\nCome and get it, suckers!
Jiang Ziya, if one could merely call out to\nfish and expect them to come, fishing\nwould be no challenge at—
Hee hee ha ha hee! Yep! I used a relic that\nallows me to speak to any living creature!
All of the fish in the lake are here now.\nI'm gonna fill up a bucket, then stuff that\ninside a BIGGER bucket and fill THAT!
Cursed insolence! Wretched deceit!\n...Move over. I'm fishing in your spot.
Yes, me too. Make room, you!
No way! Go find your own cheater spot!
Feline Dragon Who Loves to Fish
How can you possibly fish without ME?\nYou KNOW it's my favorite thing!\n...Now everybody shove over.
Heeeere, fishy fishy fishies!\nI'm gonna catch you and eeeat you!
What the fins is going on here?\nI'm not catching ANYTHING!
We may have overfished this lake.
Yeah, I sorta used my powers to summon\nall the fish and then we caught all the fish\nand then... Well, you know how it goes.
I do NOT ＂know how it goes!＂\nAnd your plan was simply horrid!
First you ditch me, then you starve me\nof my favorite food? Hissssss!
Thaniel? Jiang Ziya? There is still\nthe matter of our little competition.
Ah geez, we've each got a zillion fish.\nMaybe we just call it a draw?
A fine idea. I'll gut them and trim them\nso we can all enjoy a proper feast.
Of course not. Consider it our amends\nfor failing to invite you in the first place.
Oh, and if we ever do this again,\nwe'll TOTALLY bring you along!
As the sun set, the four friends enjoyed the bounty\nof the lake and the remainder of their day off.
Mmmm-eow! This sashimi is delectable!\nNow for the grilled fish...
(Looks like the fish got the cat's tongue...)
